# FQCN Standards

Apply these rules on **every** task, role, playbook, plugin, and export template change.

## Ansible builtins and includes

- Tasks and includes: `ansible.builtin.*` (for example `ansible.builtin.import_role`, `ansible.builtin.include_tasks`, `ansible.builtin.set_fact`, `ansible.builtin.uri`, `ansible.builtin.template`).
- Never use bare module names (`import_role`, `uri`, `set_fact`) or legacy `include` without `ansible.builtin`.

## Red Hat Satellite collection

- Modules and roles: `redhat.satellite.<module_or_role>` (for example `redhat.satellite.product`, `redhat.satellite.content_views`).
- Prefer `ansible.builtin.import_role` with `name: redhat.satellite.<role>` when a matching role exists.

## This collection

- Roles: `infra.satellite_configuration.<role>` (for example `infra.satellite_configuration.filetree_read`, `infra.satellite_configuration.global_vars`).
- Modules: `infra.satellite_configuration.<module>` (for example `infra.satellite_configuration.format_yaml`).
- **Role meta dependencies** must use FQCN:
  ```yaml
  dependencies:
    - role: infra.satellite_configuration.global_vars
  ```
- **`include_role` / `import_role` name** must use FQCN when referencing collection roles:
  ```yaml
  ansible.builtin.include_role:
    name: infra.satellite_configuration.global_vars
    tasks_from: resolve_satellite_target.yaml
  ```

## Collection filters (critical in Jinja templates)

`ansible.builtin.template` does **not** inherit the play `collections:` context for filter resolution on ansible-core 2.16+.

Always use the collection FQCN prefix for custom filters inside `.j2` templates:

```jinja2
{{ value | infra.satellite_configuration.satellite_configuration_contains_template_markers }}
{{ base | infra.satellite_configuration.satellite_configuration_merge_by_key(overrides, 'name') }}
{{ layout | infra.satellite_configuration.satellite_configuration_sanitize_partition_table_layout }}
```

Short filter names fail at template render time with "Could not load filter".

## Playbooks

- Declare `collections:` including `infra.satellite_configuration` and `redhat.satellite`.
- Use `ansible.builtin.import_role` with `name: infra.satellite_configuration.<role>`.
- When `module_defaults` references `satellite.*`, resolve `satellite_target` â†’ `satellite` in a **prior play** (see `playbooks/run_filetree_read.yaml`).

## YAML document end (mandatory)

ansible-lint rule **`yaml[document-end]`** (and `.yamllint` `document-end: present`) require a document-end marker on Ansible YAML files.

- End **every** task, handler, playbook, and role YAML file under `roles/` and `playbooks/` with `...` on its own final line.
- Applies to primary files (`satellite_<domain>.yaml`, `get_<domain>.yaml`, `main.yaml`) **and** helper includes (`*_batch.yaml`, `wait_for_*.yaml`, `api_call.yaml`, `read_contents.yml`, etc.).
- When creating or editing any of these files, verify the last non-empty line is `...` before committing (pre-commit ansible-lint will fail otherwise).
- Jinja export templates (`.j2`) that emit full CaC documents also end with `...` after the `satellite_<resource_plural>:` block.

```yaml
- name: Example task
  ansible.builtin.debug:
    msg: done
...
```

## Forbidden for new work

- `theforeman.foreman.*`
- Short role names in `meta/main.yml` (for example `role: global_vars`)
- Short filter names in export templates
